---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import Canopy from '../components/Canopy.astro';
---
<BaseLayout
  title="Colophon — Alfred Birkelund"
  description="Privacy, corrections, and contact."
>
  <Canopy />
  <article class="essay reading">
    <header class="essay__header">
      <h1 class="essay__title">Colophon</h1>
    </header>

    <div class="essay__body">
      <h2>Privacy</h2>
      <p>
        No cookies, no analytics, no tracking pixels, no embedded widgets.
        Fonts are self-hosted, so rendering a page doesn't send any request
        to Google or a third-party CDN. Reading the site means your browser
        asks GitHub's servers for HTML, CSS, and fonts — and that's the
        whole exchange.
      </p>
      <p>
        The one third-party connection is the email subscribe form. If you
        use it, the form posts to a small Cloudflare Worker, which uses
        <a href="https://resend.com">Resend</a> to send you a confirmation
        email and — once you click the link — adds your address to a Resend
        audience. You stay there until you unsubscribe; every newsletter
        has an unsubscribe link.
      </p>
      <p>
        GitHub, like any web host, keeps short-lived access logs (IP, user
        agent, request path) for the purpose of operating the service. I
        don't have access to those logs, and nothing on this site is
        designed to identify or profile visitors.
      </p>

      <h2>Corrections &amp; contact</h2>
      <p>
        If you have any amendments, questions, or concerns, please email me at
        <a href="mailto:alfredbirkelund@gmail.com">alfredbirkelund@gmail.com</a>.
      </p>

      <p class="meta">Last updated: April 2026.</p>
    </div>

    <footer class="essay__footer">
      <a href="/">← Home</a>
    </footer>
  </article>
</BaseLayout>
